Motion for Sentence Modification

Defendant Akeem R Jenkins in court with attorney James Edgar Toran.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, with Huber release privileges for work and elder care.  Court allows for good time credit and has no objection to electronic monitoring.    

-Court waived Court costs and all applicable assessments as defendant is paying Court costs and all applicable assessments on COUNT 2; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-Court WAIVED DNA sample as defendant is providing a DNA sample on COUNT 2; defendant to pay the related surcharge during term of probation on COUNT 2; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment  

Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on February 10, 2017 by 5:00 p.m.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 1, with credit for 4 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
-Restitution set at $737.54 payable to Custom Cellular payable during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment 
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable assessments during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-Cooperate with any correctional programs recommended
-Follow all rules of probation
-Pay all supervision fees; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment 
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain full-time employment 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-No contact with Custom Cellular 
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or illegal drugs
-No use of prescription medications without a valid prescription

Defendant Akeem R Jenkins in court with attorney James Edgar Toran.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY to the amended charges.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the amended information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
